sql:
SELECT pub_id, title
FROM publications
WHERE citation_count = (
    SELECT MAX(citation_count)
    FROM publications
);

external_knowledge:
- "academic seafarers" refers to authors;
- "Harvard University vessel" refers to the institution 'Harvard University';
- "cast their nets into theSpringer Nature ocean" means published in journals published by 'Springer Nature';
- "more than five times" indicates a COUNT(*) > 5;
- "wealth of their harvest" refers to the total number of publications;
- "arranging this treasure by the wealth of their harvest" refers to ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC.

sql:
SELECT p.title, p.view_count
FROM publications p
ORDER BY p.view_count DESC;

SELECT author_id, COUNT(pub_id) as num_publications
FROM publication_authors
GROUP BY author_id;

external_knowledge:
- "genres" refers to types of publications;
- "golden stars in the sky" is a metaphor for the highly viewed publication types;
- "command the most admiration" indicates the total view counts of publications;
- "shining view counts" means the sum of view counts for each publication type.
